Brandan Eugene Reynolds is South Africa’s most prolific editorial cartoonist. Since 2002, he has been drawing the daily editorial cartoon for the national newspaper Business Day as well as contributing weekly cartoons to the Sunday Times and its supplement, Business Times. He is a member of the international organization Cartooning for Peace. He lives and works in Cape Town, South Africa. He can be found on Twitter as @brandanrey If you’re an illustrator or graphic artist with an idea for The Illustrated City series, email us at Cities@theguardian.com Follow Guardian Cities on Twitter, Facebook and Instagram to join the discussion, catch up on our best stories or sign up for our weekly newsletter